Following Apple’s announcement that it is killing its AirPort wireless router range, the company has detailed what Wi-Fi routers users should buy. Apple’s “Choosing a Wi-Fi router to use with Apple devices” page lists essential features for a Wi-Fi router to use with a Mac, iPhone, iPad, Apple TV or other Apple device. “For the most compatibility, reliability, and performance when used with Apple devices, look for a Wi-Fi router that offers these features,” said Apple. The router features are: “A traditional, single router is suitable for the size and layout of most home environments. For areas that are larger or more difficult to cover, mesh Wi-Fi systems offer flexible coverage, with multiple nodes,” said Apple. Apple also provides guidance on how to set up your router and access points.